<paragraph blockId="15.[178,1085,219,646]" pageId="15" pageNumber="404">
Description of female: Bodylength 
<quantity box="[731,809,344,366]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. Colour: Black, pronotum red, tegula and basal sclerite of fore wing reddish. Tergite I-II with grey band of pubescence, as large as half length of tergite. Wings brownish, and transparent (darker than in male). Morphology: Apical clypeal margin widely rounded. Malar space present, someone shorter than midocellar diameter. Gena and vertex long, genae 0,6x as long as width of eye. Crossing between propodeal dorsum and declivity rounded, declivity with dense pubescence, structure not visible due to preparation of specimen.
</paragraph>
